OL,4,CWinston Irvine's prison sentence
OL,5,Cdoubled
OL,7,FThe barrister claimed Irvine's crimes
OL,8,Fwere a "gross breach" of the
OL,9,Fconfidence placed in him by those who
OL,10,Fprovided the character references
OL,11,Fwhich should have been treated as an
OL,12,Faggravating factor.
OL,14,F"It somewhat defies logic that his
OL,15,Foffences were dealt with in a lesser
OL,16,Fway," Mr Murphy submitted.
OL,18,F"He has betrayed community trust by
OL,19,Fthe commission of these offences."
